<segmentation> ʔiyax̌a=’aƛ=s skuˑla-’eːʔis
<gloss> be.at=NOW=INDIC.1SG school-going.to
<translation> ‘ I was going to school there . ’

<line_2> wiʔibaqstiƛ̓itduˑ duˑwiqsubitdis .
<segmentation> wiʔiba-aqstiƛ=’it=duː duˑwiqsu=(b)it=dis 
<gloss> angry-inside.MOM=PINV=1PL father=PAST=POSS.1PL
<translation> ‘ Our father got angry at us . ’

<line_3> ʔuˑduˑʔaƛ̓itid ʔucaˑyeˑʔit Tacoma .
<segmentation> ʔu-aˑduːƛ=’aƛ=’it=id ʔu-ca-yaːp=’it Tacoma
<gloss> X-because=NOW=PINV=INDIC.1PL X-go.to-CAUS.MOM=PINV Tacoma
<translation> ‘ And this is why he sent us to Tacoma (boarding school) . ’

<line_4> ʔiyax̌ax̌aƛid ʔux̌c teʔiłpałšʔaƛ .
<segmentation> ʔiyax̌a-x̌=’aƛ=id ʔux̌c teʔił-pał-šiƛ=’aƛ
<gloss> be.at-while=NOW=INDIC.1PL there sick-time.of-MOM=NOW
<translation> ‘ We were there (when) the time of sickness began . ’

<line_5> qaˑx̌kʷačʔaƛ x̌ax̌adʔał qʷiyuqey hiyuˑʔaƛ diƛaˑk .
<segmentation> qax̌-kʷa-čiƛ-[L+S]=’aƛ x̌ax̌adʔał qʷiyu=qeyu hiyuˑ=’aƛ diƛaˑk
<gloss> dead-apart-MOM-GRAD=NOW very when=COND.3SG finish=NOW fighting
<translation> ‘ Many started dying when they stopped fighting (after the war) . ’

<line_6> ʔaƛasub ʔusiyuˑʔaƛʔu yałax̌qeys skuˑl .
<segmentation> ʔaƛasuba ʔu-siyuːƛ=’aƛ=(b)u= ̊i yała-x̌=qey=s skuˑla
<gloss> eight X-die.MOM=NOW=PAST=INDIC.3SG where-while=COND=1SG school
<translation> ‘ Eight passed away where I was going to school . ’

<line_7> ʔuˑšsuˑqstʔaƛ duˑwiqsubitdis sukwiƛ̓eˑʔisaƛ̓itduˑ wałsaˑʔaƛ̓itduˑ ʔuˑduˑƛ ʔuˑšsuˑqƛx̌ duˑbey .
<segmentation> ʔuˑš-(k)suˑqstiƛ=’aƛ duˑwiqsu=(b)it=dis su-kwiƛ-’eːʔis=’aƛ=’it=duː wał-saːp=’aƛ=’it=duː ʔu-aˑduːƛ ʔuˑš-(k)suˑqƛ=x̌ duˑbeyu
<gloss> some-in.body.MOM=NOW father=PAST=POSS.1PL get-MOM-going.to=NOW=PINV=1PL go.home-CAUS.MOM=NOW=PINV=1PL X-because some-in.mind=SUBOR always
<translation> ‘ Our father got worried , (so) he came to get us and brought us home because he was always worried . ’

<line_8> wik̓aƛitdiš teʔiłšiƛ .
<segmentation> wik=’aƛ=(b)it=diš teʔił-šiƛ
<gloss> not=NOW=PAST=ASSER.1PL sick-MOM
<translation> ‘ But we didn’t get sick . ’

<line_9> wałšʔaƛduˑ wikaƛduˑ huʔiy .
<segmentation> wał-šiƛ=’aƛ=duː wik=’aƛ=duː hu-ʔiya
<gloss> go.home-MOM=NOW=1PL not=NOW=1PL again-get.to.be.at
<translation> ‘ We went home and never went back . ’

